  "texts": [
    "But they do not warrant accurate, reliable outputs that can be used for technical communication work.",
    "These practices do not guide users to an effective prompt and, as a result, may present a learning curve when interacting with such tools.",
    "Moreover, the prompts generated by current practices often neglect context and rhetorical devices, leading to scattered, undirected outputs of which do not pertain to the writer's focus.",
    "Such practices, therefore, present an element of unpredictability and offer limited control on communicators, who are forced to continuously aim directionless at their targets, hoping to accidentally wander into their desired output.",
    "Overall, the literature suggests many directions for how to improve prompt engineering."
  ],
